-- find peripherals
local ctrl = peripheral.find("rotation_speed_controller")
if not ctrl then error("Rotation Speed Controller not found") end

local stress = peripheral.find("stressometer")
if not stress then error("Stressometer not found") end

-- controller parameters (tweak these!)
local Kp = 200           -- proportional gain: higher → more aggressive response
local maxSpeed = 256     -- max RPM (clamped)
local minSpeed = 1       -- min RPM (clamped)

-- initialize
local targetSpeed = ctrl.getTargetSpeed() or 0
ctrl.setTargetSpeed(targetSpeed)

-- control loop
while true do
  -- read stress
  local currentStress  = stress.getStress()
  local capacity       = stress.getStressCapacity()
  local ratio          = currentStress / capacity

  -- compute error (we want ratio → 1.0)
  local err = 1 - ratio

  -- proportional adjustment
  local delta = math.floor(Kp * err)
  if delta == 0 then
    -- ensure at least ±1 RPM change when off-target
    delta = err > 0 and 1 or -1
  end

  -- update and clamp speed
  targetSpeed = math.min(maxSpeed, math.max(minSpeed, targetSpeed + delta))
  ctrl.setTargetSpeed(targetSpeed)  -- apply new speed :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}

  -- feedback
  print(string.format(
    "Stress: %d/%d (%.1f%%) | Speed: %d RPM",
    currentStress, capacity, ratio * 100, targetSpeed
  ))
end
